name: Kepler-269
scenarioDescription:
The Kepler-269 Exoplanetary System

Kepler-269 is a star with 0.887 times the mass of the Sun, and 0.96 times its radius. It is located 7889.16 light years away from the solar system.

Kepler-269 is known to have 2 exoplanets in orbit around it.

Kepler-269 b

Kepler-269 b was discovered by the Kepler observatory using the transit method. Its discovery was announced in 2014-03. Its semi-major axis is 0.06 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. It takes 5.33 Earth days to complete an orbit around its host star, Kepler-269.

The mass of Kepler-269 b is 8.39 times the mass of Earth. The radius of Kepler-269 b is 2.47 that of Earth. At 8.39 Earth masses, Kepler-269 b is a so called Super Earth. Super Earths could be terrestrial worlds like Earth, but they could also be ocean worlds or terrestrial worlds wrapped in a substantial atmosphere, in which case some refer to them as Mini Neptunes. No Super Earths are known to exist in our solar system, but if it exists, the so-called Planet Nine could very well be a super Earth, as it is hypothesized to have a mass between five and ten Earth masses.

Kepler-269 c

Kepler-269 c was discovered by the Kepler observatory using the transit method. Its discovery was announced in 2014-03. Its semi-major axis is 0.08 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. It takes 8.13 Earth days to complete an orbit around its host star, Kepler-269.

The mass of Kepler-269 c is 3.40 times the mass of Earth. The radius of Kepler-269 c is 1.69 that of Earth. At 3.40 Earth masses, Kepler-269 c is a so called Super Earth. Super Earths could be terrestrial worlds like Earth, but they could also be ocean worlds or terrestrial worlds wrapped in a substantial atmosphere, in which case some refer to them as Mini Neptunes. No Super Earths are known to exist in our solar system, but if it exists, the so-called Planet Nine could very well be a super Earth, as it is hypothesized to have a mass between five and ten Earth masses.
